
Overview of verb uproot

The verb uproot has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) uproot, deracinate -- (move (people) forcibly from their homeland into a new and foreign environment; "The war uprooted many people")
2. uproot, eradicate, extirpate, root out, exterminate -- (destroy completely, as if down to the roots; "the vestiges of political democracy were soon uprooted" "root out corruption")
3. uproot, extirpate, deracinate, root out -- (pull up by or as if by the roots; "uproot the vine that has spread all over the garden")
